      <p>(d) Calculate moles of O atoms. [1]</p>
      <editor-toolbar></editor-toolbar><div class="answer-area" contenteditable="true"></div>

      <p>(e) Determine empirical formula. [1]</p>
      <editor-toolbar></editor-toolbar><div class="answer-area" contenteditable="true"></div>

      <p>(f) Suggest one source of error. [1]</p>
      <editor-toolbar></editor-toolbar><div class="answer-area" contenteditable="true"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="question">
      <h3>Question 12 — First ionisation energy [4 marks]</h3>

      <table>
        <tr><th>Element</th><th>Li</th><th>Be</th><th>B</th></tr>
        <tr><td>IE₁ / kJ mol⁻¹</td><td>520</td><td>900</td><td>801</td></tr>
      </table>

      <p>(a) State trend from Li to Be. [1]</p>
      <editor-toolbar></editor-toolbar><div class="answer-area" contenteditable="true"></div>

      <p>(b) Explain why B is lower than Be. [2]</p>
      <editor-toolbar></editor-toolbar><div class="answer-area" contenteditable="true"></div>

      <p>(c) Which element is most reactive metal? [1]</p>
